Why L-shape matters

Most systems defend along the axis of flow:
	•	Is the signature valid?
	•	Is the key correct?
	•	Is the message well-formed?

But attacks / failures often come from orthogonal dimensions:
	•	timing
	•	context
	•	meaning
	•	authority mismatch
	•	sequence violations

So the L-ambush checks from the side:

“This looks valid—but does it make sense from a different axis?”

