🔍 Anubis Decision Model (Weighing the Transition)

Instead of binary allow/deny, Anubis runs a weighing ritual:

Inputs
	•	Prior state
	•	Claimed transition
	•	Mechanism used
	•	Context/timing
	•	Resulting authority

Weights (Feathers)
	1.	Continuity – does this follow expected sequence?
	2.	Coherence – does it make sense across dimensions?
	3.	Proportionality – does output authority match input?
	4.	Narrative Integrity – does the story match the mechanics?
	5.	Reversibility – can we undo this safely?

⸻

Verdict Modes
	•	⚖️ Balanced → allow
	•	🟡 Drift detected → shadow / monitor
	•	🔴 Heavy (corrupted) → halt / challenge / fork

